x4freetext: cross sections and resonance integrals of Mn,Fe,
Measurement of cross sections and resonance
.The samples were in form of solutions or plates.
.The phase oscillator method was used to measure
the thermal absorption cross-sections of materials
with small capture but big scattering cross sections.
used to measure reaction rates. Deducting the
thermal part,the resonance integral was calculated.
.For materials whose resonance parameters are well
known,the res. integrals have been also calculated.
.The error on the correction dissemination, which
comes almost exclusively from the scattering cross
.The error on the correction of self-absorption, which
is due to the uncertainty the method of calculation.
The latter has been experimentally verified, the
contribution of this error on the final result is low.
